description.value: FHIR implementation guide for the pregnancy passport in Switzerland.

valueMarkdown.value: Automatically added as a dependency - all IGs depend on the HL7 Extension Pack

description.value: This profile constrains the Appointment resource to represent the date of the planned next pregnancy examination.
This profile constrains the Composition resource to represent the first entry in the CH EPREG Document.
This profile constrains the Coverage resource to represent the insurance data.
This profile constrains the Bundle resource to represent the pregnancy passport.
This profile constrains the Encounter resource to represent a pregnancy examination from the child's perspective.
This profile constrains the Encounter resource to represent a pregnancy examination from the mother's perspective.

This extension represents the sequential number of a pregnancy-related examination (e.g., 1 = first examination, 2 = second examination, or second ultrasound). It indicates the order of occurrence within the pregnancy.
This base profile constrains the Observation resource to represent the pregnancy progress.
This base profile constrains the Observation resource to represent the laboratory results.

name.value: CH EPREG Observation (Child): Fetal Heart Feature

description.value: This profile constrains the Observation resource to represent the fetal heart feature (e.g. rate, sounds, rhythm).
This profile constrains the Observation resource to represent the movement of the fetus (e.g. activity, strength).
This profile constrains the Observation resource to represent the position of the fetus.
This profile constrains the Observation resource to represent the blood group.
This profile constrains the Observation resource to represent the fetal Rhesus D determination from the maternal blood.
This profile constrains the Observation resource to represent the birth abdominal circumference.
This profile constrains the Observation resource to represent the blood pressure.
This profile constrains the Observation resource to represent the body weight.
This profile constrains the Observation resource to represent the the height of the gravid uterus.

name.value: CH EPREG Observation (Mother): Gestational Age in Days

description.value: This profile constrains the Observation resource to represent the gestational age in days.
This profile constrains the Observation resource to represent the findings of the urine dipstick test (e.g. protein, glucose, nitrite, bacteria).
This profile constrains the Observation resource to represent the vagina feature (e.g. cervix, cervical os).
This profile constrains the Observation resource to represent the gestational weight gain.

name.value: CH EPREG Organization: Treating Healthcare Provider

description.value: This profile constrains the Organization resource to represent the treating healthcare provider.

This profile constrains the Patient resource to represent the child (fetus/newborn). (See also the [IBCM Fetal Record Profile](https://hl7.org/fhir/uv/ibcm/2024Sep/StructureDefinition-ibcm-fetal-record.html).)
This profile constrains the Patient resource to represent the pregnant individual.

name.value: CH EPREG Practitioner: Treating Healthcare Provider

description.value: This profile constrains the PractitionerRole resource to represent the treating healthcare provider.

name.value: CH EPREG PractitionerRole: Treating Healthcare Provider

description.value: This profile constrains the PractitionerRole resource to represent the treating healthcare provider.
This profile constrains the RelatedPerson resource to represent the relationship between the mother and the child.
This profile constrains the RelatedPerson resource to represent the relationship between the parent (besides the biological mother) and the child.
This value set includes SNOMED CT codes for blood group findings.
This value set includes SNOMED CT codes for fetal positions.

name.value: CH EPREG VS: Fetal RhD Antigen

description.value: This value set includes LOINC codes for the fetal Rhesus D determination.
This value set includes SNOMED CT codes for the type of parent.
